description.narrative:
The overall goal of the programme is to ensure that parliaments and their members in all parts of the world articulate and respond effectively to the needs of the people and their aspirations for peace, human rights, gender equality and development. By influencing parliaments, the IPU seeks to ensure that the voices of people, with a particular attention to marginalised groups, are heard and interests met.
To meet the overall goal, six objectives have been identified by IPU:
1. Strengthening democracy through parliaments;
2. Advancing gender equality;
3. Protecting and promoting human rights;
4. Building parliamentary support for international development goals;
5. Contributing to peace-building and conflict prevention:
6. Strengthening youth participation in parliament.
